quitreally(1)               General Commands Manual              quitreally(1)

NAME
     quitreally – diagnostic support for this feature

SYNOPSIS
     quitreally [-h] [--help] [-v] [--verbose] [--status] [--inspect APP]
                [--visible APP]

DESCRIPTION
     quitreally Query various bits of infomation about the quit really
     feature.

Commands
     ---status
              Returns information about the applications which have exited and
              left behind running non-visible children applications,
              processes, or loaded jobs.

     --inspect APP
              Returns information about the application specified by Ar APP

     --visible APP
              Returns whether the given application is visible or not.

Specifying an application
     Applications are specified either by

     name     the name of the application

     bundleIdentifier
              the bundle identifier of the application

     ASN      the ASN of a running application, specified as
              0xAAAAAAAA-0xBBBBBBBB, where A and B are hex digits

     PID      the pid of a running application

     bundle path
              the bundle path of a running application

     all      all applications

     exited   all applications which have exited but left behind

